### Test des routes invitations GECC

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### 2. Inscription d'un utilisateur (pour les tests)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "architect@test.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "fullName": "Architecte Test",
  "role": "architect",
  "companyName": "Test Company",
  "jobTitle": "Architecte"
}

### 3. Connexion
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "architect@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Créer un projet (pour tester les invitations)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/projects
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "PROJ-2024-001",
  "name": "Projet Test Invitations",
  "description": "Projet pour tester les invitations",
  "address": "123 Rue de la Paix, Paris",
  "type": "residentiel",
  "surfaceArea": 100.5,
  "ownerName": "Maître d'ouvrage Test"
}

### 5. Créer une invitation
POST http://localhost:3000/api/projects/PROJECT_ID_HERE/invites
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "membre@test.com",
  "role": "engineer"
}

### 6. Lister les invitations du projet
GET http://localhost:3000/api/projects/PROJECT_ID_HERE/invites
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Récupérer les détails d'une invitation (public)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/invites/INVITE_TOKEN_HERE

### 8. Accepter une invitation (sans être connecté)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/invites/INVITE_TOKEN_HERE/accept
Content-Type: application/json

### 9. Accepter une invitation (en étant connecté)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/invites/INVITE_TOKEN_HERE/accept
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 10. Annuler une invitation
POST http://localhost:3000/api/invites/INVITE_ID_HERE/cancel
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 11. Documentation API
GET http://localhost:3000/api/docs
